    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-08T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-08T07:00:00-05:00" n="473"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d473">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">251.11 Insull, Samuel/354: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-08T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >March 8, 1934—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 8—10:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>25. Your 15, March 7, 7 p.m. The Rumanian Legation is ready to accord visa but
                    fugitive has not applied.</p>
                <p>Since the Foreign Minister has several times asked me where the fugitive can go I
                    have passed the above information on to the Foreign Office.</p>
                <p>Insull applied this morning for a transit visa through Hungary which was not
                    granted because he refused to name country of destination; also applied for visa
                    through Syria with apparent destination Russia. French Consul has asked
                    instructions. Two days ago he applied for transit visa through Bulgaria which
                    Consul says he will grant if visa for country beyond Bulgaria is obtained
                    first.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
